# Moni – Project Overview

**Moni** is a local-first, privacy-focused personal finance app: wallets, transactions, analytics, and **on-device AI** that turns natural language, receipt photos, and (on Android) bank notifications into **reviewable transaction proposals**—processed with a local vision-language model, not a cloud API. Built as a Turborepo monorepo with two apps and shared packages.

## Monorepo Structure

```
apps/mobile/   - Expo React Native (primary user interface)
apps/web/      - Next.js 16 App Router (dashboard + REST API backend)
packages/types/     - Shared Zod schemas + TypeScript types (@repo/types)
packages/ui/        - Shared React components (@repo/ui)
packages/eslint-config/
packages/typescript-config/
```

Run commands with pnpm:
- `pnpm --filter mobile dev` / `pnpm --filter web dev` / `pnpm dev`

## Core Design Decisions

- **Local-first**: Mobile writes to SQLite first, syncs to Supabase in background
- **REST API** (not tRPC): Next.js Route Handlers at `app/api/**/route.ts`
- **Shared types**: `@repo/types` exports Zod schemas and inferred TS types — use on both client and server
- **No global state library** in Phase 1; use `useState`/`useReducer` for UI state, TanStack Query for server state

## Tech Stack Summary

| Layer | Mobile | Web |
|---|---|---|
| Framework | Expo SDK ~54, React Native 0.81 | Next.js 16 App Router |
| Routing | expo-router ~6 (file-based) | App Router |
| Styling | Tailwind via Uniwind | Tailwind CSS |
| Local DB | expo-sqlite + Drizzle ORM | — |
| Cloud DB | — | Supabase (PostgreSQL) |
| Auth | Supabase Auth + expo-secure-store | Supabase Auth |
| Server state | TanStack Query | TanStack Query |
| Validation | Zod (from @repo/types) | Zod (from @repo/types) |
| Animations | react-native-reanimated ~4 | — |
| On-device AI (mobile) | Qwen 2.5 VL 3B via `@react-native-ai/llama`; unified orchestrator → `proposed_transactions` (user review before save) | — |

## Key Conventions

- TypeScript strict mode everywhere
- All types inferred from Zod schemas in `@repo/types`; never duplicate type definitions
- Authentication: Supabase JWT Bearer token in `Authorization` header
- Error responses: `{ error: string; details?: any }` with standard HTTP status codes
- Currency amounts stored as `real` (SQLite) / `decimal(12,2)` (PostgreSQL)
- UUIDs stored as `text` in SQLite, `uuid` in PostgreSQL

## Current focus

CRUD for wallets, transactions, and categories; offline-first mobile with background sync; web dashboard with analytics. **AI:** on-device extraction and wallet resolution into pending proposals (`proposed_transactions`), with a review modal before data is committed—see `apps/mobile/lib/ai/ORCHESTRATOR.md`.
